        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We consider the host galaxy of GRB 031203 to be point-like. To resolve it against other field sources we require an angular resoution of 1 arcsec. It will not be possible to resolve individual components within the host galaxy. Therefore, we set the largest angular scale to be 0.0.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>At an observed frequency of 350GHz, the host flux is 31.80 microJansky. In order to obtain a 3 sigma detection, we require a sensitivity of 10.60microJy.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
